 deck this week" "<p><strong>Mon</strong>:  The most-cited statistics papers ever</p><p><strong>Tues</strong>:  American Psychological Society announces a new journal</p><p><strong>Wed</strong>:  Am I too negative?</p><p><strong>Thurs</strong>:  As the boldest experiment in journalism history, you admit you made a mistake</p><p><strong>Fri</strong>:  The Notorious N.H.S.T. presents: Mo P-values Mo Problems</p><p><strong>Sat</strong>:  Bizarre academic spam</p><p><strong>Sun</strong>:  An old discussion of food deserts</p><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://andrewgelman.com/2014/03/31/deck-week-6/\">On deck this week</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://andrewgelman.com\">Statistical Modeling, Causal Inference, and Social Science</a>.</p>" "http://andrewgelman.com/2014/03/31/deck-week-6/" (21305 26373) old 21 nil nil ((title nil "On deck this week") (link nil "http://andrewgelman.com/2014/03/31/deck-week-6/") (comments nil "http://andrewgelman.com/2014/03/31/deck-week-6/#comments") (pubDate nil "Mon, 31 Mar 2014 13:00:53 +0000") (dc:creator nil "Andrew") (category nil "Decision Theory") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://andrewgelman.com/?p=23065") (description nil "<p>Mon: The most-cited statistics papers ever Tues: American Psychological Society announces a new journal Wed: Am I too negative? Thurs: As the boldest experiment in journalism history, you admit you made a mistake Fri: The Notorious N.H.S.T. presents: Mo P-values Mo Problems Sat: Bizarre academic spam Sun: An old discussion of food deserts</p><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://andrewgelman.com/2014/03/31/deck-week-6/\">On deck this week</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://andrewgelman.com\">Statistical Modeling, Causal Inference, and Social Science</a>.</p>") (content:encoded nil "<p><strong>Mon</strong>:  The most-cited statistics papers ever</p><p><strong>Tues</strong>:  American Psychological Society announces a new journal</p><p><stron